race.comment: TSARINE (7) resumes for a top metro stable and went close at Ballarat at her only start last preparation. She won her Maiden here as a $2.60F prior on debut and has jumped out well here for this. Maps well and can come back further improved. REGAL TYCOON (3) was impressive second-up scoring by 2.2L at Kyneton from the speed as a firm favourite. She will be better for that and with some weight relief is sure to give a big sight. SHAALUTE (1) has won three of his last four and the latest was a tough effort from the back at Kyneton, bet $2.5F. This is a shade tougher, but the 3kg claim brings him right into it. COSTAE (4) resumes for a smart stable and won a recent Cranbourne jumpout. Has the rail and the best of her form stacks up.
